name: gridfill
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "0.3.0" %}

package:
    name: gridfill
    version: {{ version }}

source:
    fn: v{{ version }}.tar.gz
    url: https://github.com/ajdawson/gridfill/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
    md5: 4d26437253b77d756e5b37e516c63b51

build:
    number: 0
    skip: True  # [win and py3k or win64]

requirements:
    build:
        - python
        - numpy x.x
        - mingwpy  # [win]
        - gcc  # [unix]
    run:
        - python
        - numpy x.x
        - libgcc  # [unix]

test:
    requires:
        - nose
    imports:
        - gridfill

about:
    home: https://github.com/ajdawson/gridfill
    license: MIT
    summary: Fill missing values in a grid by solving Poisson's equation via an iterative relaxation scheme

extra:
    recipe-maintainers:
        - ajdawson
        - ocefpaf
